reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Soft and comfy and cute
reviews.reviewText: I loveee the material. It’s giving a tennis dress; stretchy, supportive, and comfortable. I will definitely be ordering in more colors. It is kinda short so you’re definitely gonna need to wear shorts under it. I’m 5’9, 205Lbs, D cup and I don’t need a bra in this. Will upload pics when I style it

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Very cute, but those with curves should size up
reviews.reviewText: I love this dress! Very comfortable and tight up top so no bra necessary (if you are very large-chested it could potentially be too snug though). Stretchy and thick material, no see-through issues and fabric seems durable. For me at least, the tightness around the chest and arms, coupled with the fact this it is definitely short, meant that I needed to size up. It's short enough that you don't need to worry about it being awkwardly long at a larger size, it will definitely still be a mini dress. Can be dressed up or down.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I'm 5'4" and probably around 118-120 lbs and I ordered both a size Small and size Medium. The Small was very tight and a little hard to get on and off, but the material is stretchy so if I was wanting something skin tight it would have been doable. I returned the Small and kept the Medium since the fit was a little less compression like (compared to the small) and allowed me more room to breathe (lol). Also since there's a slit in this, I felt like the length of the Medium was a little better where it came up on the Small. Love the square neck line but it's a little low where I felt like I kinda needed to keep an eye on pulling it up so that my strapless bra didn't show. Would work better with a strapless bra with low-profile cupping or probably pasties/stickies, preferably!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not chubby girl approved, though it really could've been.
reviews.reviewText: I share in what other reviewers say about how sturdy the fabric is. This dress does compress well and isn't visually see through. I am, however, returning it for the following reasons:It's not VISUALLY see-through, but the fabric is so tight you can see any shapewear or underwear underneath it, barring maybe like a full unitard, which I don't own. The muffintop at the top of tights would also show :(I can't wear a proper bra, which would be nice at my size and build. The square neckline is very wide and the bra will show no matter what. I do like the styling of a wide neck, and I think it keeps the dress from being too boring, but with how unforgiving the tight fabric is I don't feel confident letting my tig ol biddies do whatever they want. The seem to want to sit in my armpits in this dress.On me, this comes VERY short. XL is my standard size--there was nothing for me to size up to--and I feel like more size options would've made me exchange this instead of returning it.If you're midsized (US size 12) or smaller and comfortable with little-to-no structure underneath,, this is a well-constructed and gorgeous little dress. You should size up for more breathing room!The airy blue is true to color and very feminine and flattering. I'll come back if they ever add more sizes!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect compression feeling
reviews.reviewText: I love this product. It definitely is a tad but tight but in a good way feeling on my arms and upper torso. I probably would have orders a large to see if it fit a little more natural in the upper body. BUT I will still wear the Medium. It fits perfectly. Super soft. Feels like the Lu Lu lemon align material with the compression.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Beautiful flirty yet tasteful dress. Wore it with a sticky bra to show less lines. The dress has spandex and holds you nicely. I got a size small. I’m 5 feet and about 120 pounds. Fits like a glove. I got the light blue. I love it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Didn’t Work for Me
reviews.reviewText: I wanted to love this dress so badly! The style is very cute and material was super soft and comfortable. It’s so hard to find clothes that are double lined up top so you that you can go braless while still feeling secure! But unfortunately this dress was not big boob friendly and fit SO tightly across my chest that they were practically at my chin and I was spilling over. Other than the super small chest area the rest of the dress fit perfect in my normal size. I would definitely still recommend it to anyone that’s smaller up top for a more subtle push up look!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Love love love
reviews.reviewText: I’m 5’, 165, between 36-38 bra, wide shoulders and I bought the Large but am retuning it for the XL. It’s gorgeous!!! It does run small but it’s worth the attempt to squeeze into it!!! It’s so cute!!! And the top part really is shaping. Very true about the “no bra needed”. The material is thick but comfortable. The length is perfect for me, not to short not too long (keep in mind, I’m 5’). I would call the sleeves compressing vs tight. My arms are a little thick and the sleeves made them look slim. I can’t wait to get the XL!!! I would definitely do two sizes up if you are big chested. I’m on the sm/md boob size and they barely fit.

Es un vestido que da una forma muy linda, estira un poco y las tallas son reales, pide según tus medidas.Tiene 2 capas de tela muy resistentes y hace sentir y ver como si tuvieras una faja. No hay necesidad de usar brasier con este vestido pues las mantiene muy bien en su lugar.Yo soy copa 34DDD, con cintura de 78 y cadera de 110 y el L me quedó perfecto. Tuve que comprar también en blanco porque la calidad es muy buena y en ambos colores se mantiene el corte y la estética. Se ha vuelto mi vestido favorito
This dress is everything I wanted love the feel and the stretch. The only thing is that it’s short . I’m 5”7 or 172 cm, i got a xl and I had to wear shorts underneath.

Me gusta pero no me encanta. Vi reseñas que decían que subiera una talla más pero en lo personal me quedó muy grande, y muy largo para mi gusto. En la imagen tuve que mandar a hacerle arreglos para que se ajustara a como lo quería, entonces revisen muy bien sus medidas. Fuera de eso es un excelente vestido, doble forraje y tela de calidad
